article.headline: Ill.-Chicago 71, N. Illinois 48
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Josh Mayo scored 16 points and Othyus Jeffers had 14 as Illinois-Chicago beat Northern Illinois 71-48 Tuesday night. Jovan Stefanov and Spencer Stewart each added 13 points for the Flames (5-4), who shot an even 50 percent through both halves. Stefanov pulled down a team-high six rebounds, while Stewart dished five assists. Northern Illinois (3-2) got 12 points from reserve Quintan Lipkins and 11 from Cody Yelder. Center James Hughes didn't score, but grabbed a game-high seven rebounds. Illinois-Chicago got off to a quick start and never lost the lead, taking a 39-17 advantage into halftime. The Huskies shot 12-for-23 (52 percent) in the second half, but couldn't overcome the early deficit.
